<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./PeteyLeinonen">PeteyLeinonen</a>: In the Paths of the Dead, I killed a zombie Lesser Balrog, which then dropped a corpse. Lesser Balrogs don't have the DROP_CORPSE flag. <p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Ah, but it was a zombie.  I doubt the developers even considered this.  I wonder whether it's a bug or just an unintended consequence. 
</p>
<p>
It's an old alchemy secret to get a demon corpse; alchemists didn't want it fixed, either, because of how mindboggingly-hard it is to get demon corpses. 
</p>
<p>
On deep levels meats of monsters that never-ever drop corpses and can't get corpse-causing egos have been known to appear(Ghost meat can even be eaten!); I have some meat of ghost with my current char. I hope it's enough to brand my upcoming weapon artifact; I don't think I can get a ghost corpse ever. (-; 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ZizzoTheInfinite">ZizzoTheInfinite</a>: Hmm, does the Paths of the Dead change the rules for monster ego types?  Because the entry for Zombie in <tt>re_info.txt</tt> has a <tt>F:DROP_CORPSE</tt> line, which AIUI means the Zombie ego can't be added to a monster unless it already has the <tt>DROP_CORPSE</tt> flag --- so the Zombie Lesser balrog shouldn't have been possible in the first place. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./PeteyLeinonen">PeteyLeinonen</a>: I forgot to mention, that I killed a normal Lesser Balrog only 50 or so steps before. I don't recall a corpse being dropped with that kill. I'm not sure if the two are related. 
</p>
